Delicious!! Super fresh, clearly homemade food. I got the veggie enchiladas, and instead of them just being cheese and beans, or mushy microwaved frozen vegetables, they were full of fresh vegetables that were still a bit crisp. Green sauce was just a bit spicy, wish I had gotten the spicier red sauce. But it was still delicious and had actual complex flavor beyond just spice. Even if this place wasn't crammed into a weird little triangle on the hellstrip that is Hamilton Ave., I would still be amazed at the high quality of their food. But given the awkward location challenges they contend with, I am in awe of what they can accomplish.

I am always on the hunt for authentic Mexican food. Coming from San Diego I literally grew up on it. I've driven by the place a few times and the sign in the window saying we have tamales sealed the deal. Today I did my usual buffet (no personal changes to items) of a carnitas burrito: Excellent!! Two fish tacos which turned out to be salmon: Excellent! Two cheese and jalapeño tamales: Great! Two chicken and green sauce tamales: great! All the tamales were very fresh and well made!! The 2 chicken Gorditas plate was entirely home made while I waited: Excellent!!! The side of guacamole was Awesome!! Their salsa, as I understand it, are all home made and all were very flavorful! The red salsa was very close to my all time favorite.... besides mine of course I'm moving up north in two weeks but I assure you I'll return here several times before I move  and if i'm ever near I'll make it part of my trip! It's that good. Everything together was $41.
